paper_title.en: EXPERIMENTAL STUDY ON EFFECT OF REINFORCEMENTS AT WEB CONNECTED PARTS OF WF BEAM TO SHS COLUMN CONNECTIONS

description.ja: In this paper, the static characteristics of WF beam to SHS column connections that beam web connected parts were reinforced were investigated by cyclic loading test. The methods of reinforcement were inserting horizontal diaphragm or vertical stiffener inside panel zone. The main parameters were type of reinforcements, width-to-thickness ratio of the column and type of web connection. The test results shows that by reinforcing of web connected parts the maximum strength and the plastic deformation ability of the beam-to-column connection are getting better. The reasons are that the out-of-plane deformation of the column is restrained enough and the bending moment carrying ratio of web connected parts becomes large by reinforcement.

paper_title.en: EXPERIMENTAL STUDY ON THE STATICAL CHARACTERISTICS OF PERIMETER BEAM-TO-SHS COLUMN CONECTIONS USING VERTICAL STIFFENER PLATES

description.ja: In this study, the statical characteristics of perimeter beam-to-SHS column connections using vertical stiffener plates (C-VS type connections) are experimentally investigated. The test results showed that C-VS type connections could transfer the stress of the beam to panel zone by vertical stiffeners and the statical characteristics of them were almost equivalent to the usual connections. In this test series effective area of the panel zone under severe cyclic loading are investigated experimentally using cruciform specimens. The panel strength ratio Rpp (pMp/Min (ΣbMp,ΣcMp) of specimens were designed less than 1. The other side panel zone without vertical stiffeners could carry only one third times stress from beam as much as that of vertical stiffeners side. But, it seemed that the expansion of the effective length of the panel zone with vertical stiffeners side and the reinforcing effect of vertical stiffeners made up for this imbalance between the both sides. Therefore it is possible to evaluate an effective volume of the panel zone of C-VS type connection the same as usual connection.
